<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/world-bank-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="Internal wrangle threaten world bank education project in Taraba" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> By Femi Bolaji Facts have emerged of an internal wrangle in the circle of the World Bank assisted State Education Programme Investment Project, SEPIP, in Taraba State. Vanguard investigation revealed that a communication from a staff of SEPIP in Taraba to their national office indicting the state Project Coordinator, PeterToshi raised the dust. An 11 point allegation of wrongdoing was raised against the Project Coordinator, which he has since denied when contacted. Continue reading Internal wrangle threaten world bank education project in Taraba at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard